import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="Species", y="Body_Mass__g_", data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Body Mass: {:.2f}'.format(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x="Beak_Length__mm_", y="Body_Mass__g_", data=data, hue="Species", palette="deep")
    chart.axhline(y=data['Body_Mass__g_'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Body Mass')
    chart.axvline(x=data['Beak_Length__mm_'].mean(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Mean Beak Length')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between beak length and body mass?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Flipper_Length__mm_', hue='Island', multiple='stack', kde=True)

    plt.legend(title='Island')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.catplot(x="Species", hue="Sex", kind="count", data=data, palette="pastel")
    chart.set(title='What is the gender distribution among the penguin species?')
    chart._legend.set_title('Gender')
    chart._legend.set_bbox_to_anchor([1, 0.5])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
